Layer 2: Cognitive Modeling
  - Learning style adaptation
  - Stress response prediction
  - Decision pattern analysis

Layer 3: Operational Support
  - Procedure automation
  - Anomaly detection
  - Scenario simulation

Layer 4: Ethical Sentinel
  - Constraint checking against ethical frameworks
  - Intervention recommendation
  - Explanation generation for decisions
```

5.2 Evolution Timeline

Year 1: "The Tutor"

· Learns student's knowledge gaps
· Adapts teaching style in real-time
· Builds cognitive model

Year 2: "The Mirror"

· Begins to anticipate needs
· Automates routine tasks
· Provides decision support

Year 3: "The Partner"

· Co-designs solutions with student
· Challenges assumptions
· Manages lower-level systems

Year 4: "The Extension"

· Predictive intervention
· Autonomous subsystem management
· Seamless human-AI cognition

5.3 Trust Calibration Protocol

Weekly Drills:

· Monday: AI provides 3 "confident errors" during routine operations
· Wednesday: 2-hour "dead stick" exercise (no AI assistance)
· Friday: Review of AI override decisions from the week

Metrics Tracked:

· Intervention accuracy (catching AI errors)
· Override appropriateness (when student overrides AI)
· Recovery time from system failures
· Stress levels during AI vs. human decision-making

6.0 NEURO-COGNITIVE CONDITIONING

6.1 Prefrontal Cortex Development Protocol

Daily Regimen:

```
06:00-06:30: Morning neuro-feedback session
  - EEG monitoring during meditation
  - Real-time feedback on focus metrics
  - Goal: Achieve "cold cognition" state within 5 minutes

16:00-16:30: Afternoon cognitive control training
  - Stress-inducing simulations
  - Heart rate variability biofeedback
  - Goal: Maintain analytical thinking under cortisol spike

22:00-22:15: Evening review with neuro-coach
  - Analysis of day's cognitive performance
  - Planning for next day's challenges
```

Weekly Enhancements:

· Transcranial Direct Current Stimulation (tDCS) for focus improvement
· Neuro-feedback games for impulse control
· Sleep optimization via polysomnography and adjustment

6.2 Circadian Manipulation Protocol

Variable Day-Length Schedule:

· Month 1: 24-hour Earth-normal cycle
· Month 2: 24.5-hour cycle (simulating Mars)
· Month 3: 29.5-hour cycle (simulating lunar day)
· Month 4: Irregular cycle (mission simulation)

Light Therapy Implementation:

· 10,000 lux blue-spectrum at "dawn"
· Progressive amber shift toward "dusk"
· Complete darkness during sleep periods
· Emergency lighting that doesn't disrupt circadian rhythm

6.3 Stress Inoculation Graduation

Phase 1 (Months 1-6): Predictable Stressors

· Scheduled difficult tasks
· Known failure modes
· Instructor support available

Phase 2 (Months 7-12): Unpredictable Stressors

· Random system failures
· Conflicting priorities
· Limited instructor support

Phase 3 (Months 13-18): Compound Stressors

· Multiple simultaneous emergencies
· Communication blackouts
· Equipment limitations
· No instructor support

Phase 4 (Months 19-24): Existential Stressors

· Simulated life-threatening situations
· Ethical dilemmas with no good solutions
· Complete isolation periods
· Resource exhaustion scenarios

