B.6 LEARNING OBJECTIVE DATABASE STRUCTURE

Each of the 5,000 learning objectives follows format:

```
LO-ID: PHY-2037-048
Description: Calculate radiation shielding requirements for mixed particle types
Bloom's Level: Apply (Level 3)
Associated Missions: LUN-2030-047, LUN-2032-015, LUN-2035-022
Assessment Method: Simulation performance, written calculation, peer review
Mastery Threshold: 90% accuracy under time pressure
Prerequisite LOs: PHY-2035-019, PHY-2036-033
Next LOs: PHY-2038-012, MED-2040-007
AI Tutoring Module: RAD-SHIELD-TUTOR-04
Common Misconceptions: Overestimating aluminum effectiveness against neutrons
Real-World Applications: Spacecraft design, nuclear medicine, radiation therapy
```

Bloom's Taxonomy Distribution:

· Remember: 15% (facts, procedures)
· Understand: 20% (concepts, principles)
· Apply: 25% (procedures in new situations)
· Analyze: 20% (break down, organize, differentiate)
· Evaluate: 15% (judge, critique, justify)
· Create: 5% (design, construct, plan)

