E.2 FACULTY TRAINING PROGRAM

Phase 1: Foundation (Months 1-3)

```
Week 1-2: LAEP Philosophy and Ethics
  - Study complete LAEP blueprint
  - Ethics board orientation
  - Legal responsibilities training

Week 3-4: Systems Familiarization
  - Habitat operations certification
  - Life support systems training
  - Emergency procedures

Week 5-8: Teaching Methodology
  - Convergence curriculum workshop
  - AI-assisted teaching tools
  - Assessment and evaluation training

Week 9-12: Immersion Experience
  - 30-day habitat residence
  - Participate as student in basic training
  - Teach one module under supervision
```

Phase 2: Specialization (Months 4-6)

· Track-specific training
· Industry partner site visits (NASA centers, SpaceX, etc.)
· Research project development
· Teaching portfolio creation

Phase 3: Integration (Months 7-12)

· Co-teach with experienced faculty
· Develop original curriculum components
· Pass comprehensive examination
· Receive final teaching certification

Ongoing Development:

· Annual 2-week intensive update
· Quarterly skill refresh workshops
· Monthly research seminars
· Required publication: 1 peer-reviewed paper every 2 years

