E.4 PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT PATHWAYS

Academic Track:

```
Year 1-3: Assistant Professor
  - Focus: Teaching mastery, course development
  - Requirements: Teach 4 courses/year, 1 publication

Year 4-7: Associate Professor
  - Focus: Research leadership, curriculum innovation
  - Requirements: Lead research team, develop new course

Year 8+: Full Professor
  - Focus: Institutional leadership, field advancement
  - Requirements: Department chair, international recognition
```

Operational Track:

```
Year 1-3: Training Specialist
  - Focus: Mastery of training systems
  - Requirements: Certify in all training modalities

Year 4-7: Mission Director
  - Focus: Complex mission design and execution
  - Requirements: Lead 3 capstone missions

Year 8+: Program Architect
  - Focus: Whole-program design and improvement
  - Requirements: Redesign major curriculum component
```

Research Track:

```
Year 1-3: Research Scientist
  - Focus: Individual research projects
  - Requirements: 2 publications/year

Year 4-7: Principal Investigator
  - Focus: Leading research teams, securing grants
  - Requirements: $1M in external funding

Year 8+: Research Director
  - Focus: Setting research agenda, institutional partnerships
  - Requirements: Establish international collaboration
```

Cross-Training Requirements:

· All faculty must spend 2 weeks/year in another track
· Annual rotation through different teaching roles
· Required to mentor junior faculty and students
· Must maintain operational certifications

External Engagement:

· 1 month/year at industry partner facility
· Required participation in professional societies
· Public outreach requirement: 4 events/year
· Government advisory opportunities

